added.title: My Name Is Jose
added.description: The Titans have Raven give them new super powers but have a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Quantum Fun
added.description: Robin takes the other Titans on a trip through the dizzying world of quantum physics.

added.title: Nostalgia Is Not a Substitute for an Actual Story
added.description: The Titans time travel back to the 1980s to determine whether or not it was the best decade ever.

added.title: Crowbar Jones: Origins
added.description: Grizz pitches his Crowbar Jones prequel film to Nom Nom, hoping Nom Nom will agree to appear in the movie.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: The Re-Run
added.description: When we last saw Gumball, he was hitting rewind on Rob's Universal Remote just in time to save himself from being trapped in The Void. The remote has now taken Gumball back to the beginning of that disastrous day. Armed with the knowledge of what this day has in store, he must try and stop Rob from destroying his life.

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The Uncle
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are desperate to meet Ocho's famous uncle.

added.title: The Singing
added.description: The town of Elmore becomes an all-singing, all-dancing mash up. Everyone has a song inside them, but do they really need to be heard?

added.title: The Worst
added.description: Each member of the family thinks their demographic has it the toughest. Gumball and Darwin think guys have it the worst.  Mom thinks women do.  Anais thinks kids do.  And Dad thinks that grown-ups do. They decide the only way to figure it out is to spend a day in each other's shoes, no matter if they're too-small, too-big, or high-heeled.

added.title: Safari Sa'Bad
added.description: On their trip to Adrenaworld West, Ben takes a detour on a jungle cruise and finds himself hunted by the evil Tim Buktu. Our hero must outwit the baddie if he wants to make it off the amusement park ride alive!

added.title: The Nature of Things
added.description: While sightseeing at the Geyser Gulch National Park, the Tennyson trio uncover Steam Smythe's steam-powered generator and must shut it down before it overloads the power grid or, even worse, causes a massive earthquake that destroys the entire park!

added.title: Reststop Roustabout
added.description: With the Rustbucket stopped on the Midwest roadside, Ben locks himself inside with his tablet as Max and Gwen enjoy the great outdoors, until Team Tennyson is pulled into a wild Jack-a-Lope chase.

added.title: That's the Stuff
added.description: While touring a space museum, Ben's excitement multiplies when he learns that recently discovered space stuff is being examined inside the museum's lab. Once the stuff comes to life and the shape-shifting goo replicates our hero, Ben must look within if he is to stop the case of mistaken identity.

added.title: The Feels
added.description: While Max and Gwen revel in the holiday spirit of Winter Wonderland, Ben couldn't be more unamused and focused on the toys, but once the Weatherheads set their sights on Winter Wonderland as their next target, our hero must become one with his emotion if he is to save the town.

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: There Are No Hoppy Endings
added.description: Chef struggles to maintain his sanity when the kids continue to blame a stuffed rabbit named Hoppy for everything they do wrong.

added.title: Too Much of a Goo'd Thing
added.description: Beth refuses to believe that the adorable goo creature she's created out of slime is consuming the kids until she and Gwen are the only two left in class.

added.title: The Price of Advice
added.description: After a paper origami fortune teller tells Izzy she's the world's best advice giver, she's determined to prove it.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple helps Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion struggle to ride Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple needs to be tall so that he can be in love.

added.title: Positive Attitude Theory
added.description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: The Boy Who Cried Lechuza
added.description: After faking an injury to get out of work, Vic gains sympathy from everyone while unknowingly attracting attention from a dangerous mythical creature.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: The Last of the Formlings
added.description: Akita tells the story of the "Choosing" and how she, and her twin brother, Kataru, went into the wilds to discover their animal forms.

added.title: My Enemy, My Friend
added.description: The Ice Emperor's terrible Ice Dragon strikes again, laying waste to the Ice Fisher's village, forcing the ninja to go after Lloyd…

added.title: The Kaiju Protocol
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Wu and Pixal attempt to locate the Never-Realm, and accidentally unleash a dreaded creature from the Departed Realm…

added.title: Corruption
added.description: The story of Zane's arrival in the Never-Realm and how he fell under the sway of the villainous Vex.

added.title: A Fragile Hope
added.description: Having discovered the terrible truth of Zane's fate, Lloyd finds himself imprisoned and alone in the clutches of the Ice Emperor.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: #ScrambledEggs
added.description: It's egg-xactly what you think: the home economics "Egg-Baby" assignment, where students are paired up and given an egg to "care for" over a weekend. But when tragedy befalls egg after egg, what should be an easy assignment escalates into a madcap romp with super-high stakes!

added.title: #DramaQueen
added.description: Oliver Queen must face off against his greatest rival yet, Mortimer Drake, while Green Arrow also finds himself up against a new foe, The Cavalier.

added.title: #AllyCat Part 1
added.description: When Zee Zatara realizes Lex Luthor has unearthed a magical book with the power to tell the future, the girls reluctantly enlist Catwoman to help them steal it from him before he understands what he has, but it may already be too late.

added.title: #AllyCat Part 2
added.description: When Zee Zatara realizes Lex Luthor has unearthed a magical book with the power to tell the future, the girls reluctantly enlist Catwoman to help them steal it from him before he understands what he has, but it may already be too late.

added.title: #Retreat!
added.description: Jessica Cruz and some super friends go on an overnight camping trip without their powers and are attacked by Poison Ivy and a horde of Plant Zombies!

added.title: ThunderDogs
added.description: The Thundercats agree to foster a demonic puppy from the Astral Plane until they can find it the perfect owner. But could the perfect owner be their worst enemy? Their worst enemy is Mumm-Ra in case you forgot!

added.title: Mini Mongor
added.description: The Thunderkittens unleash a demon who is powered by fear. Too bad he's small and not that scary.

added.title: Swampy Johnny
added.description: The Thundercats invite a super cool swamp man into the Cat's Lair who is on the run from some scary looking aliens!

added.title: Tygra's Garden
added.description: Tygra says he's done being a Thundercat after he gets engaged to a sentient flower. Now it's up to Lion-O to break up the wedding!

added.title: The Space Beam
added.description: The new rulers of Plun-Darr say they'll bring one of the Mutants home; whichever one of them activates a homing beacon that will blow up the Thundercats. Now it's every Mutant for themselves as they battle it out to be the one to activate the beacon!

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Mama Said
added.description: When King of Ooo sends Finn and Jake on a mission to catch flying mushrooms, they find their loyalty tested.

added.title: James II
added.description: Finn and Jake discover Clone James has been faking his own death to collect medals. But there are 25 Jameses running amok!

added.title: Little Brother
added.description: Shelby is thrust into a new role after a party-related accident.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Jermaine
added.description: After a chilling dream encounter, Finn & Jake are determined to reconnect with their reclusive brother.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Kitty & Hawk
added.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

added.title: Bedtime Stories
added.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

added.title: Dunklecorn
added.description: A mysterious relative, Uncle Donklecorn, shows up unexpectedly, claiming to be family. Hawkodile thinks it's just Master Frown and Brock in a donkey costume, trying to ruin things as usual, but Unikitty and Puppycorn are convinced Donklecorn is an old family member. Hawk follows his bodyguard senses and tries to prove that Donklecorn is a fake, until finally the real Master Frown and Brock show up and ruin things, just as he suspected they would. He admits he was wrong about Uncle Donklecorn, but all is forgiven and the friends dance it out together.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Firstbourne
added.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

added.title: Primogenita
added.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Hierro y piedra
added.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Iron & Stone
added.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.

added.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
added.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

added.title: Radio Ninjago libre
added.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: How to Build a Dragon
added.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

added.title: Como construir un dragon
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Gilded Path
added.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

added.title: El camino dorado
added.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Doctor Visit
added.description: Uncle Grandpa hates going to the doctor but he's overdue for an important vaccination.

added.title: Me Llamo Jose
added.description: Raven les da nuevos superpoderes a los Titanes, pero a ellos les cuesta adaptarse.

added.title: Diversion Cuantica
added.description: Robin lleva a los demás Titanes a un viaje a través del vertiginoso mundo de la física cuántica.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: La Nostalgia No Es Un Substituto Para Una Historia Moderna
added.description: iLos Titanes viajan en el tiempo hasta los años 80 para determinar si realmente fue la mejor década de la historia!

added.title: Exquisite Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa has been having some truly bizarre night terrors.

added.title: Cowbar Jones: Origines
added.description: Pardo presenta la precuela de su película de Crowbar Jones a Nom Nom, con la esperanza de que acepte actuar en la película.

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: Public Radio
added.description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: Officer Moody
added.description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

added.title: Just Wait in the Car
added.description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: En flashes retrospectivos al pasado lejano, vemos una aventura de Charlie en el desierto mexicano.

added.title: Missing Cat
added.description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: Los Osos bebé se inscriben en un torneo de lucha libre mexicana.

added.title: The Trade
added.description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal.

added.title: Lil' Mac
added.description: Mr. Gus' nephew terrorizes Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve.

added.title: KO, Rad, and Enid!
added.description: When confronted with their lack of a team gimmick, KO, Rad, and Enid wonder what their group identity should be.

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Skips Strikes
added.description: Skips reveals himself to be an excellent bowler, until he realizes he has to bowl Death's team.

added.title: Slam Dunk
added.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

added.title: Rap It Up
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby don't want Pops to be called a loser so they say that they'll join him in a rap battle.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: Red Action 3: Grudgement Day
added.description: KO and Enid attempt to prevent a mysterious power battle between Rad and Red Action.

added.title: Skips vs. Technology
added.description: Skips wants to help Mordecai and Rigby with their computer problems.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: Small World: Stone Cold Spider Part 2
added.description: With Townsville in peril, the girls are sent to the arctic on a dangerous mission to find the key to saving the day.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Replaced
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that Benson is going to replace them and have to figure out a way to stop it.

added.title: The AB Bakugan Battle League!
added.description: With all the mayhem and destruction Haavik is causing, the Awesome Brawlers decide that a bit of Bakugan brawling is the perfect distraction to take their minds off all the trouble. With the help of some friends, they start the Awesome Brawler Bakugan Battle league!/ The Awesome Brawler's Bakugan Battle league rages on. Just as the semifinal round comes to a close, an uninvited guest crashes the party, bringing an alarming end to the battle league.

added.title: Haavik's Challenge/Storm Haavik's Tower
added.description: Haavik's Challenge: Haavik has crashed the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan League, and challenges the Awesome Brawlers in a battle league of his own!/ Storm Haavik's Tower: In order to keep Earth and Vestroia safe and rescue Drago, the Awesome Brawlers agree to enter Haavik's Bakugan Battle League, and race toward Haavik's tower for the final showdown.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Kitty y Halcon: Protectores de la Ley
added.description: Cuando el juguete favorito de Perricornio desaparece, Unikitty y Halcondrilo se unen para localizar al ladrón, ial estilo socios policías! Pero cuando las cosas se ponen difíciles y el caso no se resuelve, ya no es solo su sociedad la que está en juego, sino también su amistad.

added.title: Sidekick Scouts
added.description: KO gets more than he bargained for when he gets a sidekick.

added.title: Los Safaris son Malos
added.description: En su paseo a Adrenaworld West, Ben toma un desvío por una selva y descubre que lo persigue el malvado Tim Buktu. iNuestro héroe debe ser más listo que el villano si quiere llegar al parque de diversiones con vida!

added.title: La Naturaleza de las Cosas
added.description: Mientras pasean por el Parque Nacional Geyser Gulch, el trío Tennyson descubre un generador a vapor de Steam Smyth y debe apagarlo antes de que sobrecargue la red eléctrica o, peor, icause un terremoto masivo que destruya el parque entero!

added.title: Parada de Descanso
added.description: Con el Rustbucket detenido en la carretera del Medio Oeste, Ben se encierra con su tablet mientras que Max y Gwen disfrutan del hermoso paisaje, hasta que el equipo Tennyson debe involucrarse en una persecución salvaje de un jackalope.

added.title: Es la cosa
added.description: Mientras visita un museo espacial, la emoción de Ben se multiplica cuando se entera de que están examinando en el laboratorio unas "cosas espaciales" que acaban de descubrir. Pero cuando esa cosa viscosa cobra vida y comienza a replicar a nuestro héroe con su capacidad de cambiar de forma, Ben debe buscar en su interior si quiere detener el caso de identidad equivocada.

added.title: El sentimiento
added.description: Mientras Max y Gwen se deleitan en el espíritu navideño de Winter Wonderland, Ben no podría estar más aburrido y concentrado en los juguetes. Pero cuando los Weatherheads fijan sus miras en Winter Wonderland como su próximo objetivo, nuestro héroe debe conectarse con sus emociones si quiere salvar la ciudad.

added.title: Triquicornio
added.description: Un misterioso pariente, el tío Triquicornio, aparece inesperadamente asegurando ser de la familia. Halcondrilo cree que solo son Master Frown y Brock en un disfraz de burro tratando de arruinar las cosas, pero Unikitty y Perricornio están convencidos de que Triquicornio en un viejo miembro de la familia. Halcondrilo sigue sus instintos de guardaespaldas e intenta probar que Triquicornio es un impostor.

added.title: Ayudantes Scouts
added.description: KO obtiene más de lo que esperaba cuando consigue su propio ayudante.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Dolores del crecimiento
added.description: Perricornio está cansado de que Unikitty siempre lo ayude y ya no quiere ser el hermano pequeño, así que usa un poco del dulce de crecimiento de la Dra. Fox para ser más grande que Unikitty.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 1
added.description: Sgt. Night publicly criticizes Dr. Light's views on human & robot unity during a school assembly, invoking the ire of Fire Man and forcing Silicon City's newly minted hero, Mega Man, to intervene.

added.title: Throwing Shade Part 2
added.description: Mega Man stops Fire Man by replicating his powers and fighting fire with fire. Unfortunately, Mega Man also learns that he can replicate a robot's mental state as well, and must get his own anger under control to win. Defeated, Fire Man reports back to his secret master, Sgt. Night!

added.title: Drilling Deep
added.description: At school, Aki struggles with the side effects of his newly replicated Drill Man schematics; later, as Mega Man, he learns to control his Fire Powers in thwarting Drill Man's assault on Skyraisers Inc.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: La Invitacion
added.description: Craig y sus amigos están invitados a una exclusiva merienda con deliciosos postres, si es que pueden quedarse hasta el final de la fiesta.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Bros in Space
added.description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

added.title: A Real Steal/Lightning Unleashed
added.description: A Real Steal: Dan embarks on a solo adventure to outdo Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers and winds up having to be saved by them instead./Lightning Unleashed: Lightning uncovers the Mind Core Cell buried beneath the Earth and battles Stata the Hunter in an effort to protect its secret.

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: El ultimo nino en el Arroyo
added.description: Por una terrible maldición, Craig se convierte en el único niño del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Conejo culpable
added.description: Chef intenta conservar su cordura cuando los niños culpan repetidamente a un conejo de peluche llamado Saltarín de todo lo que ellos han hecho.

added.title: Demasiada baba
added.description: Beth se niega a creer que la adorable criatura de baba que ha creado con limo esté comiéndose a los niños hasta que ella y Gwen son las únicas dos que quedan en la clase.

added.title: El precio de un consejo
added.description: Cuando una esfera de la fortuna de origami le dice a Izzy que es la mejor consejera de vida del mundo, está decidida a probar que es así.

added.title: Un Triunfo Robado
added.description: Dan se embarca en una aventura para superar al nuevo equipo de Peleadores Bakugan de Magnus, pero al final, ellos lo salvarán a él.

added.title: La Aventura de Lightning
added.description: Lightning descubre la Célula Núcleo enterrada bajo tierra, y se enfrenta a Strata El Cazador para intentar proteger su secreto.

added.title: Un Gran Enfrentamiento
added.description: Lightning por fin revela la ubicación de la Célula Núcleo, pero cuando Los Fantásticos llegan, descubren que Magnus fue más rápido que ellos.

added.title: La Batalla Decisiva
added.description: Luego de que la Célula Núcleo pusiera en estado de hibernación a los Bakugan de ambos equipos, Dan y Magnus se encuentran atrapados en una batalla donde lo apostarán todo.

added.title: Madtrap
added.description: Madcap and Princess SugarSalt trap Axel and the team inside a Minergy-powered labyrinth that attacks them with their greatest fears, forcing them to work together and escape as a unit.

added.title: Oportunidades Laborales
added.description: Después de derrotar a Magnus, los Fantásticos reciben una oferta de empleo de alguien inesperado... Filomena Dusk.

added.title: To Tame the Perilous Skies!
added.description: With Axel's drone-wing broken, the team must find another way to stop Madcap and his minions as they take to the skies in toy airplanes for an aerial assault on the city park.

added.title: Un Nuevo Empleo
added.description: Durante un comercial para celebrar su contrato con el equipo AAAnimus, Dan y Los Fantásticos deciden rebelarse antes que traicionar sus principios.

added.title: Four Color Fallout
added.description: Axel, Galileo, and Sarge get Minergy-transported by Madcap into the pages of Axel's favorite comic book, the hero of which turns out not to be so cool after all.

added.title: Grin and Bear It
added.description: When a toothache sends Axel to the dentist, the team must fight off Princess SugarSalt, who confuses Axel's new "crown" for the real thing.

added.title: Green with Envy
added.description: When the local news interviews Uncle Andrew about his toy inventing, an envious Galileo stages a play in the park with the help of Axel and the team, only to be interrupted by an equally envious Madcap - out to steal the spotlight for himself!

added.title: Catfight
added.description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 2
added.description: As Dr. Light and Suna turn the Robot Masters against each other, Mega Man defeats and unmasks his arch nemeses, Lord Obsidian, who turns out to be Sgt. Night in disguise, and finally learns the identity of Namagem, Mega Man's long lost twin brother!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: #GatoCallejero Parte 2
added.description: Cuando Zee Zatara se da cuenta de que Lex Luthor desenterró un libro mágico que tiene el poder de predecir el futuro, las chicas le piden ayuda a Gatúbela para robárselo antes de que Lex comprenda lo que tiene en su poder. Pero puede que ya sea demasiado tarde...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: La Ultima Cambia Formas
added.description: Akita cuenta la historia de "la Elección" y cómo es que ella y su hermano gemelo, Kataru, fueron al bosque para descubrir su forma animal.

added.title: Manzana es Bajito
added.description: Manzana tiene que ser alto para poder enamorarse.

added.title: La Trampa de Madcap
added.description: Madcap y Princess SugarSalt atrapan a Axel y al equipo dentro de un laberinto impulsado por Minergy que los ataca con sus mayores temores, obligándolos a trabajar juntos y escapar como una unidad.

added.title: #LaReinaDelDrama
added.description: Oliver Queen debe enfrentarse al mayor rival al que jamás se haya enfrenado, Mortimer Drake, mientras Green Arrow se encuentra con un nuevo enemigo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #HuevosRevueltos
added.description: Gracias a la tarea de la clase de Economía Domestica, los estudiantes son emparejados y se les entrega un huevo para "cuidar" durante el fin de semana. Pero cuando la tragedia acontece huevo tras huevo, lo que debería ser una tarea fácil, ise convierte en una disparatada persecución!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Mi Enemigo, Mi Amigo
added.description: El terrible Dragón de Hielo del Emperador ataca de nuevo, arrasando la aldea de los Pescadores de Hielo, obligando a los ninjas a seguir los pasos de Lloyd.

added.title: Corrupcion
added.description: Conoceremos la historia de la llegada de Zane al Reino del Jamás y cómo cayó bajo el dominio del villano Vex.

added.title: #GatoCallejero Parte 1
added.description: Cuando Zee Zatara se da cuenta de que Lex Luthor desenterró un libro mágico que tiene el poder de predecir el futuro, las chicas le piden ayuda a Gatúbela para robárselo antes de que Lex comprenda lo que tiene en su poder. Pero puede que ya sea demasiado tarde...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Gyranoide del Futuro
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín se esfuerzan por subir a la montaña rusa más loca del parque de diversiones.

added.title: Teoria de Actitud Positiva
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín pasan un día en los zapatos de Falafel y usan su actitud positiva para demostrar que no debería estar tan malhumorado.

added.title: Efectos en Cuatro Colores
added.description: Axel, Galileo y Sarge son transportados por Minergy por Madcap a las páginas del cómic favorito de Axel, cuyo héroe resulta no ser tan genial después de todo.

added.title: Manzana, Concentrate
added.description: Manzana ayuda a Cebollín a cumplir su sueño de competir en un programa de pastelería.

added.title: Sonrie y Aguanta
added.description: Cuando un dolor de muelas envía a Axel al dentista, el equipo debe luchar contra la Princesa SugarSalt, quien confunde la nueva "corona" de Axel con la realidad.

added.title: Una Fragil Esperanza
added.description: Después de descubrir la terrible verdad del destino de Zane, Lloyd se encuentra en el calabozo, en las garras del Emperador de Hielo.

added.title: La Aventura de la Moto de Mao Mao
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao subestima por igual a sus enemigos y a sus amigos, por poco le cuesta el reino entero.

added.title: El ProtocoloKaiju
added.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Wu y Pixal intentan localizar el Reino del Jamás y liberan accidentalmente a una temida criatura del Reino de los Muertos.

added.title: Fideito
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben seguir teniendo la onda suficiente para aparecer en el video musical de su rapero favorito.

added.title: Fragmentos
added.description: Steven se dirige al bosque para entrenarse con un poderoso mentor.

added.title: A Domar Los Cielos Peligrosos
added.description: Con el ala del avión no tripulado de Axel roto, el equipo debe encontrar otra forma de detener a Madcap y sus secuaces mientras se lanzan a los cielos en aviones de juguete para un asalto aéreo en el parque de la ciudad.

added.title: #Retirada
added.description: Jessica Cruz y algunas de sus mejores amigas salen a pasar una noche de campamento sin sus poderes, iy son atacadas por Hiedra Venenosa y una horda de plantas zombis!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Sr. Universo
added.description: Greg lleva a Steven de viaje para encontrar los orígenes del nombre del Universo.

added.title: El Comienzo de Cobrangutan
added.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

added.title: Pozo de los deseos
added.description: Cuando Puppycorn utiliza una fuente de los deseos y su deseo no se hace realidad, Unikitty se sorprende al descubrir la razón: todos los deseos realizados a lo largo de los años no se pueden cumplir porque están atrapados en el fondo de la fuente (es un sistema tonto). Unikitty los libera para que traigan alegría a la ciudad, y así descubre que se echaron a perder un poco después de años atrapados en un agujero oscuro. iPronto todos desearán que todo se termine!

added.title: La Zona
added.description: A Unikitty le cuesta mantener la calma cuando juega a videojuegos y entra en La Zona, a diferencia de Puppycorn, su hermano menor. Pero un repentino accidente de laboratorio destroza su consola y ahora, para su sorpresa, el castillo se bloquea como un videojuego del mundo real, icon sus amigos como jugadores! ¿Podrá Unikitty salvar a sus amigos y dominar La Zona antes de que termine el juego?

added.title: Demasiados Unikitties
added.description: Unikitty llega a la conclusión de que todo el mundo sería mucho más feliz si pensara como ella, iy tal vez pueda lograrlo con la ayuda de la Dra. Fox! Unikitty copia sus ondas cerebrales en todos sus amigos y los Unikittyfica, para que todos puedan ser siempre positivos. Pero pronto, Unikitty se da cuenta de que puede haber un exceso de "buena princesa".

added.title: Noticias Unikitty
added.description: Estás viendo el programa de noticias del Unireino Super Good Morning Time Action Information Show, un programa de noticias variadas realizado (mal) por Unikitty y la banda: Hawkodile se encarga del clima, Puppycorn habla deportes, a pesar de no saber ninguna de las reglas, la Dra. Fox tiene un divertido segmento de cocina científica que sale mal, y Richard quiere que el programa deje de emitirse. Unikitty tiene un reportaje contundente y una gran primicia después de la pausa, isi el estudio sobrevive tanto tiempo!

added.title: Sabro Atraco
added.description: Richard preparó uno de los postres más sabrosos de todos los tiempos, pero lo cerró con llave hasta que los amigos terminen su cena aburrida. Esto no va a seguir así. Para organizar un atraco, Unikitty organiza a sus amigos como un comité de expertos para entrar, salir y comer ese sabroso bocadillo sin que Richard lo sepa. Pero este atraco tiene un traspié. ¿Podrán los amigos llevarse el pastel?

removed.title: #RageCat
removed.description: Jessica Cruz is convinced she can find the purr-fect forever home for Dexter, a cat who has been deemed unadoptable because he's basically the worst cat in the world. Her overbearing persistence in trying to get him adopted leads Dexter to become Dex-Starr, an evil Red Lantern supervillain! Can Jess still find the good in a fuzzy little nemesis who is trying to kill her?

removed.title: Make the Cut

removed.title: Melter Skelter
